704024f-a.text:
Dock Street (left) north from Front Street. In the background is the Manhattan Bridge extending to Manhattan. On the north side of Water Street between Dock and Main Street, is the 4 story warehouse Building of Arbuckle Bros.
April 4, 1938.
P. L. Sperr

704459f-a.text:
29-31 Front Street, north side, between Dock and Main Streets.
June 1926.
Brown Brothers.

704460f-b.text:
(1)
29-35 Front Street, north side, between Dock and Garrison Streets. The frame structure was once the mansion of Joshua Sands.
1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same. The frame house was built in 1786.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same, another view, showing in the center of the view the Sands house (frame). This is only half of the original structure. To the left of it is a brick building occupying the site of the demolished section of the Sands house. That building at present is occupied by the
Italian Mission of Santo Spirito.
August 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
